code.title: This level and all lower levels rejected
code.desc: The corresponding referenced-level and all its lower referenced-levels are rejected. One or more errors are reported at this reporting-level or a lower reporting- level.

code.desc: The corresponding referenced-level is acknowledged. All messages, packages, or groups at the lower referenced- levels are acknowledged except those explicitly reported as rejected at their reporting-level in this CONTRL message.

code.title: Interchange received
code.desc: Indication of interchange receipt.

data_element.name: syntaxError,Coded
data_element.desc: A code indicating the error detected.

code.title: Syntax version or level not supported
code.desc: Notification that the syntax version and/or level is not supported by the recipient.

code.title: Interchange recipient not actual recipient
code.desc: Notification that the Interchange recipient (S003) is different from the actual recipient.

code.title: Invalid value
code.desc: Notification that the value of a stand-alone data element, composite data element or component data element does not conform to the relevant specifications for the value.

code.title: Missing
code.desc: Notification that a mandatory (or otherwise required) service or user segment, data element, composite data element or component data element is missing.

code.title: Value not supported in this position
code.desc: Notification that the recipient does not support use of the specific value of an identified stand-alone data element, composite data element or component data element in the position where it is used. The value may be valid according to the relevant specifications and may be supported if it is used in another position.

code.title: Not supported in this position
code.desc: Notification that the recipient does not support use of the segment type, stand-alone data element type, composite data element type or component data element type in the identified position.

code.title: Too many constituents
code.desc: Notification that the identified segment contained too many data elements or that the identified composite data element contained too many component data elements.

code.title: No agreement
code.desc: No agreement exists that allows receipt of an interchange, group, message, or package with the value of the identified stand-alone data element, composite data element or component data element.

code.title: Unspecified error
code.desc: Notification that an error has been identified, but the nature of the error is not reported.

code.title: Character invalid as service character
code.desc: Notification that a character advised in UNA is invalid as service character.

code.title: Invalid character(s)
code.desc: Notification that one or more character(s) used in the interchange is not a valid character as defined by the syntax identifier indicated in UNB. The invalid character is part of the referenced-level, or followed immediately after the identified part of the interchange.

code.title: Invalid service character(s)
code.desc: Notification that the service character(s) used in the interchange is not a valid service character as advised in UNA or not one of the default service characters. If the code is used in UCS or UCD, the invalid character followed immediately after the identified part of the interchange.

code.title: Unknown Interchange sender
code.desc: Notification that the Interchange sender (S002) is unknown.

code.title: Too old
code.desc: Notification that the received interchange or group is older than a limit specified in an IA or determined by the recipient.

code.title: Test indicator not supported
code.desc: Notification that test processing can not be performed for the identified interchange, group, message, or package.

code.title: Duplicate detected
code.desc: Notification that a possible duplication of a previously received interchange, group, message, or package has been detected. The earlier transmission may have been rejected.

code.title: References do not match
code.desc: Notification that the control reference in UNB, UNG, UNH, UNO, USH or USD does not match the one in UNZ, UNE, UNT, UNP, UST or USU, respectively.

code.title: Control count does not match number of instances received
code.desc: Notification that the number of groups, messages, or segments does not match the number given in UNZ, UNE, UNT or UST, or that the length of an object or of encrypted data is not equal to the length stated in the UNO, UNP, USD, or USU.

code.title: Groups and messages/packages mixed
code.desc: Notification that groups have been mixed with messages/packages outside of groups in the interchange.

code.title: Lower level empty
code.desc: Notification that the interchange does not contain any messages, packages, or groups, or a group does not contain any messages or packages.

code.title: Invalid occurrence outside message, package, or group
code.desc: Notification of an invalid segment or data element in the interchange, between messages or between packages or between groups. Rejection is reported at the level above.

code.title: Too many data element or segment repetitions
code.desc: Notification that a stand-alone data element, composite data element or segment is repeated too many times.

code.title: Too many segment group repetitions
code.desc: Notification that a segment group is repeated too many times.

code.title: Invalid type of character(s)
code.desc: Notification that one or more numeric characters are used in an alphabetic (component) data element or that one or more alphabetic characters are used in a numeric (component) data element.

code.title: Data element too long
code.desc: Notification that the length of the data element received exceeded the maximum length specified in the data element description.

code.title: Data element too short
code.desc: Notification that the length of the data element received is shorter than the minimum length specified in the data element description.

code.title: Trailing separator
code.desc: Notification of one of the following: - the last character before the segment terminator is a data element separator or a component data element separator or a repeating data element separator, or - the last character before a data element separator is a component data element separator or a repeating data element separator.

code.title: Character set not supported
code.desc: Notification that one or more characters used are not in the character set defined by the syntax identifier, or the character set identified by the escape sequence for the code extension technique is not supported by the recipient.

code.title: Envelope functionality not supported
code.desc: Notification that the envelope structure encountered is not supported by the recipient.

code.title: Dependency condition violated
code.desc: Notification that an error condition has occurred as the result of a dependency condition violation.

code.title: UN/ECE level B
code.desc: As defined in the basic code table of ISO 646 with the exceptions of alternative graphic character allocations and national or application-oriented graphic character allocations.

code.title: Segment terminator

code.title: Component data element separator

code.desc: Specifies that this is the separator between data elements.

code.title: Release character
code.desc: Specifies that this is the release character.

code.title: Repetition separator

data_element.name: validationValue,Qualifier

code.title: Unique validation value
code.desc: Specifies that this is the unique validation value. This code shall be used when the algorithm involved produces a single parameter result (one MAC with DES algorithm, or one digital signature with RSA algorithm, for instance).

code.title: DSA algorithm r parameter
code.desc: Specifies that this is the r parameter, resulting of the use of DSA algorithm.

code.title: DSA algorithm s parameter
code.desc: Specifies that this is the s parameter, resulting of the use of DSA algorithm.

code.title: Random number for party A

code.title: Random number for party B

code.title: Enciphered block under a symmetric algorithm
code.desc: The result of the encipherment of data under a symmetric algorithm in an entity authentication protocol.

code.title: Enciphered block under an asymmetric algorithm
code.desc: The result of the encipherment of data under an asymmetric algorithm in an entity authentication protocol.

code.title: Key agreement value
code.desc: The value calculated in a key agreement protocol.

data_element.name: messageRelation,Coded
data_element.desc: Relationship with another message, past or future.

code.title: No relation
code.desc: The message is initial.

code.title: Response
code.desc: The message is a response message.

code.title: Response requested
code.desc: The message requests an answer.

data_element.name: securityStatus,Coded
data_element.desc: Identification of the security element (key or certificate, for instance) status.

code.title: Valid
code.desc: The security element is valid.

code.title: Revoked
code.desc: The security element has been revoked.

code.title: Unknown
code.desc: The status of the security element is unknown.

code.title: Discontinued
code.desc: The security element should not be used for ?????

code.title: Alert
code.desc: The security element has been put on alert, but is not revoked yet.

code.title: Expired
code.desc: The validity period of the security element is expired.

data_element.name: revocationReason,Coded
data_element.desc: Identification of the reason why the certificate has been revoked.

code.title: Owner key compromised
code.desc: The owner key linked to this certificate has been compromised.

code.title: Issuer key compromised
code.desc: The issuer key used to generate this certificate has been compromised.

code.title: Owner changed affiliation
code.desc: The identification details of the certificate are no longer valid.

code.title: Certificate superseded
code.desc: This certificate has been renewed and is superseded by another certificate.

code.title: Certificate terminated
code.desc: This certificate has reached the end of its validity period and has not been renewed.

code.title: No information available
code.desc: This certificate is revoked but the reason is not explicit stated.

code.title: Mutually agreed
code.desc: Mutually agreed between trading partners.

data_element.name: securityError,Coded
data_element.desc: Identifies the security error causing the rejection of the EDIFACT structure.

code.title: Wrong authenticator
code.desc: The validation is wrong.

code.title: Wrong certificate
code.desc: The certificate is wrong.

code.title: Certification path
code.desc: The certification path is incomplete. Cannot verify.

code.title: Algorithm not supported
code.desc: The algorithm is not supported.

code.title: Hashing method not supported
code.desc: The hashing method is not supported.

code.title: Protocol error
code.desc: The stated protocol has not been followed.

code.title: Security expected but not present
code.desc: It was expected the user message would be secured (eg using integrated message security or the AUTACK message in authentication mode), but this was not present or received in the expected time period.

code.title: Security parameters do not match those expected
code.desc: The parameters specifying the applied security do not match those expected (eg from an interchange agreement).

data_element.name: listParameterQualifier
data_element.desc: Specification of the type of list parameter.

code.title: Mutually defined
code.desc: Mutually defined between trading partners.

code.title: Message receiver

code.title: Certificate owner

code.title: Authenticating party
code.desc: Party which certifies that the document (i.e. the certificate) is authentic.

code.title: Alert request

code.title: Revocation list request
code.desc: Request full or partial list of revoked certificates.

code.desc: Delivery of a path.

code.title: Certificate validation notice
code.desc: Notice of validation of an existing certificate.

code.title: Revocation confirmation

code.title: Symmetric key delivery
code.desc: Delivery of symmetric keys.

code.title: Discontinuation acknowledgement
code.desc: Acknowledgement of the requested discontinuation.

data_element.name: paddingMechanism,Coded
data_element.desc: Padding mechanism or padding scheme applied.

code.title: Zero padding
code.desc: Message padding used for block cipher algorithms. Binary zeros are appended to the end of the message in order to make the message length an exact integer multiple of the block length. The block length is implicitly specified through the algorithm and mode of operation.

code.title: PKCS #1 padding
code.desc: Message padding used for block cipher algorithms according to PKCS #1 (published by RSA Inc., 1993).

code.title: ISO 10126 padding
code.desc: Message padding used for block cipher algorithms according to ISO-10126 specification.

code.title: TBSS padding
code.desc: Message padding used for block cipher algorithms according to TBSS (Swiss standard, published by Telekurs AG, 1996).

code.title: FF padding
code.desc: Message padding used for block cipher algorithms. Binary 255 are padded to fill a message up to a block length. The block length is implicit specified through the algorithm and mode of operation.

code.title: ISO 9796 #1 padding
code.desc: Message padding for digital signature schemes according to ISO 9796 part 1.

code.title: ISO 9796 #2 padding
code.desc: Message padding for digital signature schemes according to ISO 9796 part 2.

code.title: ISO 9796 #3 padding
code.desc: Message padding for digital signature schemes according to ISO 9796 part 3.

code.title: TBSS envelope padding
code.desc: Message padding for digital envelopes according to TBSS (Swiss standard, published by Telekurs AG, 1996)

code.title: PKCS #1 envelope padding
code.desc: Message padding for digital envelopes according to PKCS #1 (published by RSA Inc, 1993).

code.title: PKCS #1 signature padding
code.desc: Message padding for digital signature schemes according to PKCS #1 (published by RSA Inc, 1993).

code.title: BCS signature padding
code.desc: Message padding for digital signature schemes according to ZKA (German standard published by ZKA 1995).

code.title: OAEP
code.desc: Optimal Asymmetric Encryption Padding (published in IEEE P1363).

code.title: RSAES-OAEP
code.desc: Padding mechanism specified in PKCS#1, version2, for encryption with a RSA public key.

code.title: RSAES-PKCS#1-v1_5
code.desc: Padding mechanism specified in PKCS#1, version2, for encryption with a RSA public key.

code.title: RSASA-PKCS-v1_5
code.desc: Padding mechanism specified in PKCS#1, version2, for digital signatures.

code.title: Encryption Block Formatting
code.desc: Padding mechanism specified in PKCS#1, version 1.5.

code.title: PKCS#5
code.desc: Padding mechanism specified in PKCS#5 for symmetric encryption.

code.title: ANSI X9.23
code.desc: Padding mechanism specified in ANSI X9.23 for symmetric encryption.
